```python
class Solution:
    def numIsland(self, grid: List[List[int]]) -> int:
        m = len(grid)
        n = len(grid[0])
        
        if m < n:
            grid = [[grid[i][j] for j in range(n)] for i in range(m)]
            
        def dfs(i, j):
            visited[i][j] = True
            
            if grid[i][j]:
                self.dfs(i + 1, j)
                self.dfs(i - 1, j)
                self.dfs(i, j + 1)
                self.dfs(i, j - 1)
                
        count = 0
        
        for i in range(m):
            for j in range(n):
                if not visited[i][j] and grid[i][j]:
                    count += 1
                    
                    dfs(i, j)
                    
        return count
```
